review_res.text: I simply compare the first two fruits on the left, find out which is lighter, and put in at the left end of the row. I then compare the next fruit on the left of the row to the lighter fruit to see if it is lighter, and if it isn't, I compare it to the known heaviest fruit, and whatever is lighter goes behind the last fruit it's lighter than.
r_question:
Shortly describe your approach of the PURPLE DIAMOND for arranging

a SMALLER pile of fruits (shown on right)

in increasing weights from left to right? (180 secs to answer)

review_res.text: Same approach as before. It simply takes longer. I usually compared the new fruit on the left with the last fruit that was on the left of the row, and then go from there, comparing it to the weight of other known fruits.

review_res.text: I guess I used Strategy 2 more than Strategy one. I liked to compare the next fruit to either end of my known fruit row.
